What must be fixed in your current code

There are two real problems in the current version:

1. nv.setBooleanValue(true) is being set for any valid query string

That means any request with query params gets treated as redirect=true in doFilter().

Then this happens:

httpResponse.sendRedirect(httpRequest.getRequestURL().toString());

That redirect drops the query string, which breaks framework/resource requests like:
	•	popupPanel.css.xhtml?db=...
	•	jsf.js.xhtml?...
	•	ipsCommon.js?...

That is the main reason your page gets stuck at 99%.

2. Framework/static resource requests are being validated like business URLs

Those should be skipped entirely.

